We all know the horrors of an earthquake and we express our deep-felt sympathy for the people of the San Francisco Bay area. Private groups and officials from Tokyo to London to Charleston, SC, offered help to the ruptured San Francisco Bay area, but some said relief for the earthquake could drain coffers already strained by previous disasters. Los Angeles, long San Francisco's West Coast competitor but equally at the mercy of the San Andreas Fault, quickly shipped doctors, sonic equipment and fire investigators to the Bay Area. The mayor of a sister city in disaster, Charleston's Joseph P. 